# Repo-root .gitattributes — CONTENT owned by the Oracle Adapters HLD (§8/§2.1);
# Team #1 (crate + harness) ACTIONS its commit first in M0 because Team #1
# commits first, and it MUST land before any byte-stable artifact is added
# (Cargo.lock is already committed and is repaired here via --renormalize).
#
# core.autocrlf=true on the dev box mangles bytes on check-in unless a
# .gitattributes is in effect for the path at `git add` time. Adding it later
# does NOT fix already-staged index entries — only `git add --renormalize`
# does. This file therefore exists before metrics/snapshots/fixtures land.

# Default: text files are normalised to LF in the repo on check-in.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Byte-stable artifacts — stored verbatim, never line-ending-normalised, so
# they are byte-identical run-to-run on the declared reproducibility host
# (harness HLD §2.9; oracle HLD §3.5). Locks, schema, and HTML fixtures.
Cargo.lock -text
package-lock.json -text
benchmark/oracles/contract.schema.json -text
*.html -text
